    text "Music cognition is the interdisciplinary study of how we perceive, process, and produce music"
  ]
  node [
    id 1
    label "1"
    text " In my research, I focus on auditory prediction&#8212;how the brain anticipates musical structure in real time"
  ]
  node [
    id 2
    label "2"
    text " We use EEG and MEG to measure how violations of musical expectation elicit neural responses, particularly the mismatch negativity (MMN) and P300 components"
  ]
  node [
    id 3
    label "3"
    text " There&#8217;s growing evidence that musical training enhances cognitive functions like working memory, attentional control, and even linguistic syntax processing"
  ]
  node [
    id 4
    label "4"
    text " This isn&#8217;t just correlational&#8212;longitudinal studies suggest causality, especially when training starts early in development"
  ]
  node [
    id 5
    label "5"
    text " We&#8217;re also examining the emotional dynamics of music"
  ]
  node [
    id 6
    label "6"
    text " Music elicits powerful affective states, and we&#8217;re trying to understand how structural features&#8212;tempo, mode, harmonic progression&#8212;interact with personal memory and cultural associations to produce emotional experiences"
  ]
  node [
    id 7
    label "7"
    text " From a computational angle, we&#8217;re using probabilistic models like IDyOM (Information Dynamics of Music) to simulate expectation formation in listeners"
  ]
  node [
    id 8
    label "8"
    text " These models help us quantify 'surprise' and 'predictability' in music and compare them to neural data"
  ]
  node [
    id 9
    label "9"
    text " Another exciting area is embodied cognition&#8212;how rhythm and meter are tied to movement"
  ]
  node [
    id 10
    label "10"
    text " Motor regions in the brain are activated even when people passively listen to rhythm"
  ]
  node [
    id 11
    label "11"
    text " This has led to promising music-based interventions for motor disorders like Parkinson&#8217;s"
  ]
  node [
    id 12
    label "12"
    text " Music cognition shows us that music isn&#8217;t just entertainment&#8212;it&#8217;s a window into brain function, emotion, culture, and human connection"
